10: There is nothing so soothing as tea.
14:
We certainly had a busy night
delivering presents. Let me top you
off.
17:
There, a little taste of Yamato. \n
I hope it is to your liking.
20:
It is, Soushiro, thank you. I always
enjoy visiting Yamato.
23:
It is a place rich in both history and
culture. I could learn a thing or two
from your samurai code!
27:
The samurai code...\n
Yes, I can see how that would
appeal to you.
31:
You sound less than excited about it,
for a samurai. Have you some
qualms?
33:
"For a samurai"... It feels so long ago
that I served. I am but a simple
teacher now, Light.
46:
Th-there's a dragon! It's attacking
the kids, Soushiro—we've got to stop
it!
54: There's no time to explain! Hurry!
57: S-Sis, wake up! We have to—
72:
Collin, I need you to take Anna and
run! NOW!
103:
S-sorry, Soushiro...\n
I uh, I wasn't expecting the "dragon"
to look quite so realistic...
105: I hope it didn't scare you.
107:
The kids asked me to help surprise
you with a present.
116:
Yes. In Palpebra, it is not uncommon
for adults to receive presents.
119:
Yeah, we all worked together to get
you something for the holidays!
128:
Did... did you make this flower crown
yourselves? Oh! There's also pressed
flowers and... a portrait of me.
130:
Ahaha, look at the faces drawn on
these acorns! Our whole class is
here!
133:
Hehe, we handmade everything
ourselves! Hope you like it!
138:
I do, little one, I do. I will treasure
them all dearly...
141:
Mr. Kengyu! We've got one more
present for you.
142:
Check it out! Alk helped us make a
bunch of dorayaki for you and Mrs.
Kengyu. Make sure to leave some
out for her!
146:
I—I will.\n
...Thank you. All of you.
148:
Ahaha, you made enough to feed all
of Yamato. I think Iori and I might
need some hungry helpers.
153:
There's more than plenty to go
around—why don't we have a party?
161:
First things first.\n
...My heart is still pounding from the
scare you gave me a minute ago.
163:
That prank you pulled was VERY
naughty. Now, what do good little
girls and boys say when they do
something wrong?
172:
It's not samurai I could learn a thing
or two from—it's you!
